data.meta_description: Rosanna Arquette: Check out the list of all Rosanna Arquette movies along with photos, videos, biography and birthday. Also find latest Rosanna Arquette news on Times of India.
data.text:
#MeToo: 'Horrified' and 'finally', reaction varies on Cosby release

AP / Jul 01, 2021, 02:12 (IST)

Bill Cosby's release evoked a lot of different reactions from people. Phylicia Rashad showed joy while actor Amber Tamblyn was furious over the news of his release from prison Wednesday.

On her 60th birthday, Barbie honours 20 Sheroes and Dipa Karmakar is on the list

TNN / Mar 09, 2019, 12:13 (IST)

Dipa Karmakar, the first Indian female gymnast to win a gold medal at Olympics has made it to the list and we cannot feel more proud to welcome it to the Indian markets. Take a look at the names on the list!

Angelina Jolie throws exclusive 'Origin' celebration as Ava DuVernay's film gains momentum with high-profile backing in Oscar voting countdown

etimes.in / Jan 15, 2024, 13:26 (IST)

Aunjanue Ellis-Taylor, fresh from Jolie's residence, attended the Critics' Choice Awards, where she was nominated for Best Actress in a Drama Series for "Justified: City Primeval." The film has garnered attention from Oscar winners and industry heavyweights, with public endorsements from Ben Affleck, Regina King, Samuel L. Jackson, Dave Chappelle, and Cher, among others

Mark Blum passes away at 69 due to COVID-19 complications

ANI / Mar 27, 2020, 09:58 (IST)

According to Fox News, Blum's widow, Janet Zarish confirmed reports of Blum's death in an email and said, "My husband passed away yesterday, March 25th, from complications from the Corona Virus.

Cannes film festival condemns Harvey Weinstein sex assault

PTI / Oct 12, 2017, 11:24 (IST)

The Cannes film festival's senior executives today said sexual assault allegations against disgraced Hollywood mogul Harvey Weinstein merit "only the clearest and most unequivocal condemnation", as more women continue to come forward with accusations.

#MeToo: Harvey convicted of sexual assault, acquitted of being a serial predator

Reuters / Feb 24, 2020, 22:13 (IST)

Former Hollywood producer Harvey Weinstein was convicted of sexual assault by a New York jury on Monday but acquitted on the most serious charges that could have sent him to prison for the rest of his life. Weinstein was convicted of sexually assaulting former production assistant Mimi Haleyi in 2006 and raping Jessica Mann, a onetime aspiring actress, in 2013.

Narendra Modi, Hollande launch Ricky Kej's new music album in Paris

PTI / Dec 01, 2015, 10:20 (IST)

Prime Minister Narendra Modi and French President Francois Hollande have launched Grammy award winner, Ricky Kej's new music album 'Shanti Samsara' at the Paris climate change conference. The album features Sanskrit verses with spoken words by Amitabh Bachchan and Frances Fisher and Rosanna Arquette.
